devastated by the genocide and struggle to recover a sense of selfhood and belonging in the absence of kin, friends, and neighbors. In drawing out the contradictions at the heart of self-making and social life in contemporary Rwanda, this book asserts a novel argument about the ordinary lives caught in global post-conflict imperatives to remember and to forget, to mourn and to prosper.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCollective memoryxRwanda. 0aCollective memoryzRwanda. 0aCollective memory. 0aNational characteristics, Rwandan. 0aPeace. 0aReconciliation. 0aSelfxSocial aspectsxRwandaxButare. 0aSelfxSocial aspectszRwandazButare. 0aSelfxSocial aspects. 0aSocial conditions. 70(DE-588)4008784-00(DE-627)1043601780(DE-576)208878289aBürgerkrieg2gnd 70(DE-588)4020835-70(DE-627)1063166210(DE-576)208934987aGewaltlosigkeit2gnd 70(DE-588)4026751-90(DE-627)1062871840(DE-576)20896777XaIndividuum2gnd 70(DE-588)4032081-90(DE-627)1062629710(DE-576)208995544aKonflikt2gnd 70(DE-588)4046588-30(DE-627)10619755X0(DE-576)209070153aPolitisches Verhalten2gnd 70(DE-588)4055903-80(DE-627)1061564540(DE-576)209115866aSozialverhalten2gnd 70(DE-588)4056723-00(DE-627)1061539190(DE-576)209118741aStadt2gnd 70(DE-588)4063690-20(DE-627)1061269540(DE-576)209149884aVölkermord2gnd 70(DE-588)4112646-40(DE-627)1058356840(DE-576)209469684aAuswirkung2gnd 70(DE-588)4138354-00(DE-627)10415151X0(DE-576)209685336aLebensstil2gnd 70(DE-588)4157237-30(DE-627)1055024210(DE-576)209832878aGewalttätigkeit2gnd 70(DE-588)4190021-20(DE-627)1041605430(DE-576)210063904aWirkung2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a1990s world history.  abiographical.  aethnographic.  aethnography.  amourn.  amurdered.  anationhood.  apersonhood.  apo